If all 3 die then you lose a continue. Pretty fair.

snippet.textDisplay:
When I was a kid (like, 10-12), I was actually turned off of FF5 because there were more girls than boys, and turned off of FF6 at first because the main character you first play as was a girl. In fact, I was even turned off of Chrono Trigger﻿ because the three main characters were Chrono, Marle, and Lucca; 2 girls > one boy.
Now, I consider them to be some of the best games, once I gave them a chance. I thought I was open minded as a kid, but looking at that now, eeh...

snippet.textDisplay: I had a friend who loved this game and would show it to me when I was at his house (I was about 7-8 years old) and I really didn't like it. Why? Because I thought the boxart was ugly and I didn't like the vikings. Yep, that's reason enough to hate a game when you're a kid. This game is actually a classic puzzle platformer where you have 3 vikings and control one at a time to get around the levels. It's made by Sillicon&Synapse who later became Blizzard.
